## Project Overview

poof.sh is an environment variable storage website similar to platforms like Infisical, Dotenv Valut, Phase, and others.

### Features

- Client side encryption
- Per-project encryption system
- User's can organize variables by projects - projects by org, etc.
- User's can invite teammates to orgs/projects

### Project Structure

poof has 2 components as of now.

- `apps/web` NextJS based web app using Convex and Better-Auth. This is where the user will configure and control most things
- `apps/cli` Go based CLI tool for easy loading and unloading of env variables, all data operations (CRUD) use the Convex api routes exposed in the web app

### Tech Stack

- Web: NextJS, Shadcn/ui, Tailwind, Convex, Better-Auth
- CLI: Go, Gin
